grew a little tired, I guess,

00:22:25.184 --> 00:22:27.600
with trying to explain to these
dumb information theorists

00:22:27.600 --> 00:22:30.490
that this Kelly criterion
was not so great.

00:22:30.490 --> 00:22:33.116
So he published an
article in a journal

00:22:33.116 --> 00:22:34.740
called Journal of
Banking and Finance--

00:22:34.740 --> 00:22:38.940
that's actually a finance
journal-- where he explained

00:22:38.940 --> 00:22:41.930
why it wasn't necessarily
such a good idea

00:22:41.930 --> 00:22:44.080
to hold this portfolio.

00:22:44.080 --> 00:22:50.490
And in this article, every word
